CAPE TOWN – A firefighter has died while battling a blaze on the slopes of Table Mountain. It is believed that the woman suffered a seizure on Sunday. Cape Town Mayor Patricia de Lille took to Twitter to extend her condolences to the 33-year-old’s family. The city’s Fire and Rescue Service’s Theo Layne: “We had one adult female firefighter that had collapsed. We treated her on the scene and then she was taken to Christiaan Barnard Hospital and unfortunately she died.”